Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
uniquify_partition(25.10)                            uniquify_partition(25.10)

Name
       uniquify_partition  -  Removes  the  master  and  clone  association by
       uniquifying the cells (module) in the netlist

Syntax
       uniquify_partition

       [-help]

       -hinst <hierarchical_instance_name>

       Removes the master and clone association by uniquifying the cells (mod-
       ule) in the netlist.

       Note: You can use the undo_uniquify_partition  command  to  remove  the
       uniquification and bring back the master and clone association.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each uniquify_partition parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man uniquify_partition

       -hinst <hierarchical_instance_name>
              Specifies the name of the  hierarchical  instance  to  uniquify.
              Based  of the specified hierarchical instance, its cell (module)
              is identified. All other occurrences of the identified cell  are
              renamed  by  adding  the  _<number>  suffix  (for example  cell-
              name_<number>) in order to uniquify the cell.

              Note:

              * You  can  specify   any   hierarchical   instance   with   the
                uniquify_partition command. It does not necessarily have to be
                a master.

              * The  uniquify_partition  command  preserves the orientation of
                the hierarchical instances.

              * The uniquify_partition command preserves the pin  location  of
                the hierarchical instances.

              * A new cell name is created for each hierarchical instance.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The  following  command  identifies  the cell associated with I1/p3 and
       then renames all other occurrences of the cell in order to  remove  the
       master and clone association.

       uniquify_partition -hinst I1/p3

